<br>
a) IR is better than you think (if you DO use your pets to do damage AND if they get damage AND you want to keep up a pet all the time) - you get back more mana for a pet than you paid to summon it and it can be near death. its very close to what you get back without IR. Just a bit less.<br>
<br>
b) If you focus on petpower either have summoning quickness or a summoning time reducing item.<br>
<br>
c) Get elemental pact, before all other skills. Its not the price of malachite its pure availability of malachite. You will never care again about malachite (just need one in your backpack, partly a problem on CRs) that leeds to an excessive use of canning - you wont be sitting anymore ever ... loosing sitting aggro totally.<br>
<br>
d) Get a horse. Cheapest one if money does matter. Can only use it outdoors, but it adds 20 mana per tic while you canni.<br>
<br>
e) Now add suspend minion II.<br>
<br>
Mages who complain about manaregen have no idea how to use their mage to full extend.<br>
<br>
Canning, EP and IR (and a horse in outdoorzones) used properly in a mage-group is devastating to mobs and leaves you with no mana probs at all. I tried it ... and it is POWERFULL where pets on mobs are possible as main tanks. Can you spell DPS ???<br>
<br>
Have fun.<br>
<br>
